            <title>[FELIX-2398] Config property to disable NIO use in http.bundle doesn&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2398</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Felix-870 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-870&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-870&lt;/a&gt;) a property was added to disable the use of NIO by the jetty embedded http server. This config property no longer works. From Rob Walker:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Just grepping the source code, and I think this property was in the original felix/http.jetty bundle but may not have made it across to the new felix/http bundle.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
